    include ./parts/react-header
  body
    include ./parts/header
    main.about-page
      .container
        .about-content
          h1 About electerm

          p.about-lead electerm is a <strong>free and open-source</strong> terminal/SSH/SFTP/telnet/serialport/RDP/VNC/Spice/ftp client for Linux, macOS, and Windows.

          p Built with web technologies (Electron, React, CSS), electerm combines a full-featured terminal emulator with a graphical SFTP file manager and multiple remote connection protocols in one app. The source code is available on <a href="https://github.com/electerm/electerm" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">GitHub</a> under the MIT License.

          h2 Features

          ul
            li Works as a terminal/file manager or SSH/SFTP/FTP/telnet/serialport/RDP/VNC/Spice client
            li Supports Windows 7+ (x64/ARM64), macOS 10.15+ (x64/arm64), Linux (x64/arm64/Loong64), including older Linux with glibc 2.17+ (UOS, Kylin, Ubuntu 18.04, etc.)
            li Global hotkey to toggle window visibility (similar to Guake, default <code>Ctrl+2</code>)
            li Multi-platform (Linux, macOS, Windows)
            li <strong>14+ languages</strong> via community translations — contributions welcome at <a href="https://github.com/electerm/electerm-locales" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">electerm-locales</a>
            li Double-click to directly edit remote files
            li Authentication with publicKey + password
            li Zmodem (rz/sz) file transfer
            li SSH tunnel support
            li <a href="https://github.com/trzsz/trzsz" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Trzsz</a> (trz/tsz) support, similar to rz/sz and compatible with tmux
            li Transparent window (macOS, Windows)
            li Terminal background image
            li Global/session proxy
            li Quick commands
            li UI/terminal theme customization
            li Sync bookmarks/themes/quick commands to GitHub/Gitee secret gist, WebDAV, custom server, or electerm cloud
            li Quick input to one or all terminals
            li AI assistant integration (supporting <a href="https://www.deepseek.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">DeepSeek</a>, OpenAI, and any OpenAI-compatible API) for command suggestions, script writing, and explaining selected terminal content
            li MCP (Model Context Protocol) widget for AI assistants and external tools integration — see <a href="https://github.com/electerm/electerm/wiki/MCP-Widget-Usage-Guide" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">MCP Widget Usage Guide</a>
            li Deep link support: open connections via URLs like <code>telnet://192.168.2.31:34554</code> or <code>ssh://user@host:22</code>
            li Command line usage — see <a href="https://github.com/electerm/electerm/wiki/Command-line-usage" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">wiki</a>

          h2 Quick Links

          .about-links-grid
            .about-link-card
              h3 📖 Documentation
              p Full documentation on the official wiki.
              a.about-link(href='https://github.com/electerm/electerm/wiki', target='_blank', rel='noreferrer') Visit Wiki ↗
            .about-link-card
              h3 🎥 Video Guides
              p Watch tutorials and demos.
              a.about-link(href='/videos') Watch Videos ↗
            .about-link-card
              h3 🐛 Report Issues
              p Found a bug? Let us know.
              a.about-link(href='https://github.com/electerm/electerm/issues', target='_blank', rel='noreferrer') Submit Issue ↗
            .about-link-card
              h3 💬 Discussions
              p Join the community conversation.
              a.about-link(href='https://github.com/electerm/electerm/discussions', target='_blank', rel='noreferrer') Join Discussion ↗

          h2 Install

          p electerm can be installed in several ways:

          h3 macOS
          pre
            code brew install --cask electerm

          h3 Windows
          p Via winget:
          pre
            code winget install electerm.electerm
          p Or via Scoop:
          pre
            code.
              scoop bucket add dorado https://github.com/chawyehsu/dorado
              scoop install dorado/electerm

          h3 Linux
          p Via Snap:
          pre
            code sudo snap install electerm --classic
          p From Debian repository (Debian/Ubuntu-based systems):
          p
            a(href='https://electerm-repos.html5beta.com/deb', target='_blank', rel='noreferrer') https://electerm-repos.html5beta.com/deb
          p From npm:
          pre
            code npm i -g electerm

          h2 Development

          p electerm is built with Node.js and Electron. Requirements: Node.js 24.x.

          pre
            code git clone git@github.com:electerm/electerm.git
            br
            code cd electerm
            br
            code npm config set legacy-peer-deps true
            br
            code npm i
            br
            br
            code # start vite dev server (requires port 5570)
            br
            code npm start
            br
            br
            code # in a separate terminal session run app
            br
            code npm run app

          h2 Support the Project

          p electerm is open-source and maintained by <a href="http://html5beta.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">ZHAO Xudong</a>. You can support the project through:

          ul
            li
              a(href='https://github.com/sponsors/electerm', target='_blank', rel='noreferrer') GitHub Sponsors
            li
              a(href='https://ko-fi.com/zhaoxudong', target='_blank', rel='noreferrer') Ko-fi
            li WeChat donation (scan QR code on the home page)

